[ Screeching ]

11
00:00:49.584 --> 00:00:51.920
[ Farting ]

12
00:00:51.953 --> 00:00:53.922
[ Music playing ]

13
00:00:53.955 --> 00:01:00.929
♪♪

14
00:01:00.962 --> 00:01:02.329
'Sup. baby?

15
00:01:02.730 --> 00:01:10.972
♪♪

16
00:01:11.005 --> 00:01:12.907
[ Hissing ]

17
00:01:12.941 --> 00:01:19.146
♪♪

18
00:01:19.179 --> 00:01:21.616
Let's do some liquor science.

19
00:01:22.115 --> 00:01:24.519
Um. hey. Rick.

20
00:01:24.752 --> 00:01:26.821
Rick!

21
00:01:26.854 --> 00:01:28.923
Rick!
Are you ignoring me?

22
00:01:28.957 --> 00:01:31.593
Hey! Hello!
Rick!

23
00:01:31.993 --> 00:01:34.127
Did you go deaf?

24
00:01:34.161 --> 00:01:35.697
[ Gasps ]
No. no. no. no. no!

25
00:01:35.730 --> 00:01:37.732
Oh. my God!

26
00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:40.535
[ Clattering ]

27
00:01:40.568 --> 00:01:42.402
Whoa!

28
00:01:42.436 --> 00:01:44.271
[ Alarm ringing ]
Morty! What the fuck?

29
00:01:44.304 --> 00:01:45.974
I didn't --
I didn't mean to!

30
00:01:46.007 --> 00:01:48.509
What the fuck?

31
00:01:48.543 --> 00:01:51.980
Tell me why you ignored a sign
that said "do not disturb."

32
00:01:52.013 --> 00:01:53.447
I -- it's not
important.

33
00:01:53.480 --> 00:01:56.084
It better be. You just destroyed
my distillery.

34
00:01:56.116 --> 00:01:58.987
So either it's an emergency.
or it's important.

35
00:01:59.020 --> 00:02:00.755
And it better be
real fuckin' important

36
00:02:00.788 --> 00:02:04.291
because this was the most
important thing to me today.

37
00:02:04.324 --> 00:02:09.530
So what did you come down
here for?

38
00:02:09.564 --> 00:02:11.331
I was wondering
if you could drive me

39
00:02:11.365 --> 00:02:14.167
to pick up some Pokemon cards.

40
00:02:15.003 --> 00:02:16.269
I'm sorry.

41
00:02:16.303 --> 00:02:18.171
Have you ever seen
me happy. Morty?

42
00:02:18.205 --> 00:02:21.141
What? Uh. I mean.
not really.

43
00:02:21.174 --> 00:02:22.610
Well. I've been happy
in my life.

44
00:02:22.644 --> 00:02:25.046
And. look.
there's no point on the chart

45
00:02:25.079 --> 00:02:27.015
where my joy intersects
with your presence.

46
00:02:27.048 --> 00:02:28.248
Then why
hang out with me?

47
00:02:28.281 --> 00:02:30.018
I don't know.
When I found you.

48
00:02:30.051 --> 00:02:31.418
you were bait.
When I killed that fish.

49
00:02:31.451 --> 00:02:32.987
maybe I should have cut
the line.

50
00:02:33.021 --> 00:02:35.657
Because all I have now
is a fucking worm.

51
00:02:35.690 --> 00:02:40.061
You told me that wasn't true.
You're just trying to hurt me.

52
00:02:40.094 --> 00:02:41.129
[ Sobbing ]

53
00:02:41.161 --> 00:02:43.531
Morty. no. I meant...

54
00:02:43.564 --> 00:02:45.265
Fuck!

55
00:02:45.733 --> 00:02:46.701
God damn it.

56
00:02:46.734 --> 00:02:49.070
This would be the perfect time
for a drink.

57
00:02:49.103 --> 00:02:57.045
♪♪

58
00:02:57.078 --> 00:03:05.586
♪♪

59
00:03:05.620 --> 00:03:13.761
♪♪

60
00:03:13.795 --> 00:03:19.600
♪♪

61
00:03:21.569 --> 00:03:23.470
Pressure reader.
Fermentation chamber.

62
00:03:23.504 --> 00:03:26.206
Copper lining. Wow.
Morty blew all this up?

63
00:03:26.239 --> 00:03:27.441
What's a mash tun?

64
00:03:27.474 --> 00:03:29.043
Just get an empty beer keg
for that.

65
00:03:29.077 --> 00:03:30.511
I'll also need
60 gallon drums.

66
00:03:30.545 --> 00:03:32.180
Okay. Up front.
I'm gonna buy myself some

67
00:03:32.212 --> 00:03:33.981
shit since
I'm running your errand.

68
00:03:34.015 --> 00:03:35.149
Deal.

69
00:03:35.183 --> 00:03:36.316
Ooh.
Can I get a little surprise?

70
00:03:36.349 --> 00:03:38.485
No. The Amex automatically
blocks you. Jerry.

71
00:03:38.519 --> 00:03:40.154
How does it know
I'm using the card?

72
00:03:40.188 --> 00:03:41.823
Because of the kind of stuff
you buy.

73
00:03:41.856 --> 00:03:42.990
What do I buy?

74
00:03:43.024 --> 00:03:44.525
Dumb stuff.
Dumb stuff.

75
00:03:45.927 --> 00:03:47.595
Computer. replace potato.

76
00:03:47.628 --> 00:03:52.100
Computer: <i>The only Grimaldian</i>
<i>potato in the galaxy is here.</i>

77
00:03:52.133 --> 00:03:53.801
God damn it!

78
00:03:55.002 --> 00:03:56.170
Let's go.

79
00:03:56.204 --> 00:03:57.939
No. thanks. You're just gonna
yell at me.

80
00:03:57.972 --> 00:03:59.874
Morty. what if I told you
I have a thing that'll make it

81
00:03:59.907 --> 00:04:02.176
so you never hear me scream
at you again?

82
00:04:02.210 --> 00:04:05.813
Wait. For real?
What kind of thing?

83
00:04:05.847 --> 00:04:07.181
Rick. what the hell?!

84
00:04:07.215 --> 00:04:10.450
Oh! Ah!
[ Wailing ]

85
00:04:12.120 --> 00:04:13.453
Rick.
what did you do?

86
00:04:13.487 --> 00:04:15.255
It's a Sympathid.
a species

87
00:04:15.288 --> 00:04:17.191
that generates
unlimited empathy in its hosts.

88
00:04:17.225 --> 00:04:18.358
No matter what I say or do.

89
00:04:18.391 --> 00:04:20.260
the Sympathid
will gloss over it

90
00:04:20.293 --> 00:04:22.130
like a Disney edit
of a slasher movie.

91
00:04:22.163 --> 00:04:23.231
Here. watch.

92
00:04:23.263 --> 00:04:24.699
You're a worthless piece
of shit. Morty!

93
00:04:24.732 --> 00:04:26.200
I'm so disappointed in you.
Rick. fuck you!

94
00:04:26.234 --> 00:04:27.869
I can still hear
you screaming.

95
00:04:27.902 --> 00:04:31.139
Okay. it must need to burrow
a little bit deeper.

96
00:04:31.172 --> 00:04:32.405
There we go.
Let's try again.

97
00:04:32.439 --> 00:04:35.176
You're a piece
of sh...

98
00:04:35.209 --> 00:04:36.644
...work. Morty!

99
00:04:36.677 --> 00:04:38.646
Like a golden retriever.
A Rick's best friend.

100
00:04:38.679 --> 00:04:40.681
And when I call you
a disappointment.

101
00:04:40.715 --> 00:04:43.383
it's because I believe you can
be so much better than you are.

102
00:04:43.416 --> 00:04:45.485
How's that?
Pretty good. huh?

103
00:04:45.520 --> 00:04:47.221
It nibbles on your
empathy centers

104
00:04:47.255 --> 00:04:48.790
and poops out something
much stronger.

105
00:04:48.823 --> 00:04:51.559
Wait. It eats my empathy?
Don't worry.

106
00:04:51.592 --> 00:04:54.294
We'll only keep it in long
enough to win a potato together.

107
00:04:54.327 --> 00:04:56.230
Wait. We have to win one.
How do we --

108
00:04:56.264 --> 00:04:57.865
By dancing
with the stars!

109
00:04:57.899 --> 00:04:59.033
[ Grunting ]

110
00:04:59.066 --> 00:05:00.101
Oh!

111
00:05:00.134 --> 00:05:01.202
[ Grunting ]

112
00:05:01.235 --> 00:05:02.737
[ Gasps ]

113
00:05:02.770 --> 00:05:04.572
[ Grunting ]

114
00:05:07.909 --> 00:05:08.976
Uh...

115
00:05:10.111 --> 00:05:11.279
Hey. It's okay.

116
00:05:11.311 --> 00:05:12.647
Focus on my hips.

117
00:05:12.680 --> 00:05:14.248
That's where my center
of gravity is.

118
00:05:14.282 --> 00:05:15.716
I don't know. Rick.

119
00:05:15.750 --> 00:05:17.151
You've got this.
I believe in you.

120
00:05:17.185 --> 00:05:18.686
You two are up.

121
00:05:18.719 --> 00:05:21.522
Announcer: And now performing
"Claier de Lune: Epic Remix"

122
00:05:21.556 --> 00:05:23.925
from the "Godzilla: King
of the Monsters" trailer.

123
00:05:23.958 --> 00:05:27.795
Rick Sanchez
and his partner Morty Smith.

124
00:05:27.829 --> 00:05:35.169
♪♪

125
00:05:35.203 --> 00:05:42.710
♪♪

126
00:05:42.743 --> 00:05:50.084
♪♪

127
00:05:50.117 --> 00:05:56.657
♪♪

128
00:05:56.691 --> 00:05:59.694
Huzzah! A triumph in movement.

129
00:05:59.727 --> 00:06:01.494
Rick. I did it!
I caught you.

130
00:06:01.529 --> 00:06:03.030
I knew you could do it.
buddy!

131
00:06:03.064 --> 00:06:05.365
Announcer: Congratulations.
newest champions.

132
00:06:05.398 --> 00:06:07.501
Here is your reward.

133
00:06:07.535 --> 00:06:10.338
One perfect
Grimaldian potato.

134
00:06:10.370 --> 00:06:12.240
And did you see
when we nailed that triple spin?

135
00:06:12.273 --> 00:06:14.642
Your timing was
metronomic. Morty.

136
00:06:14.675 --> 00:06:17.511
And then when
I caught you -- oh.

137
00:06:17.545 --> 00:06:21.315
Oh. all of that
was the Sympathid. wasn't it?

138
00:06:21.349 --> 00:06:23.351
Did we actually
dance or...

139
00:06:23.383 --> 00:06:25.820
The dancing was real.
The trust. the connection.

140
00:06:25.853 --> 00:06:27.521
not so much.

141
00:06:27.555 --> 00:06:29.389
It was real nice to
to feel like that with you.

142
00:06:29.422 --> 00:06:31.259
Well. it can't stay
in there forever.

143
00:06:31.292 --> 00:06:32.560
There's a bit of
a comedown.

144
00:06:32.593 --> 00:06:34.362
What kind of
comedown -- aah!

145
00:06:34.394 --> 00:06:36.330
[ Moans ]

146
00:06:36.364 --> 00:06:38.366
I feel like shit.

147
00:06:38.398 --> 00:06:40.501
Wow. it's so nice outside.

148
00:06:40.534 --> 00:06:41.969
Stop guilting me!

149
00:06:42.003 --> 00:06:44.305
Oh. my God.
This is our fifth Home Depot.

150
00:06:44.338 --> 00:06:46.274
I'm tired of depots.

151
00:06:46.307 --> 00:06:47.842
I'm not going home
without those drums.

152
00:06:47.875 --> 00:06:49.710
It's the last thing
we need on Grandpa Rick's list.

153
00:06:49.744 --> 00:06:52.313
Maybe we should
have done all the Rick shopping

154
00:06:52.346 --> 00:06:53.948
before we went
Summer shopping.

155
00:06:53.981 --> 00:06:56.083
I wasn't going to miss out
on that Gucci x Kellogg's drop.

156
00:06:56.117 --> 00:06:59.287
Also. I didn't know everyone was
gonna be out of 60 gallon drums.

157
00:06:59.320 --> 00:07:00.888
[ Thudding ]

158
00:07:00.922 --> 00:07:01.923
What the shit?

159
00:07:01.956 --> 00:07:03.624
That dude's hoarding
all the drums!

160
00:07:03.658 --> 00:07:05.526
Why is this guy
such a drum hog?

161
00:07:05.559 --> 00:07:07.795
I'm looking for the Petco.
My dog needs...

162
00:07:07.828 --> 00:07:08.663
Ah!

163
00:07:08.696 --> 00:07:10.364
Summer:
Oh. he's a serial killer.

164
00:07:10.398 --> 00:07:12.400
Jesus!
We go to rescue that girl.

165
00:07:12.432 --> 00:07:13.534
We got to
call the cops.

166
00:07:13.567 --> 00:07:14.568
Are you kidding?
Those drums are evidence.

167
00:07:14.602 --> 00:07:16.237
The cops will take them all.

168
00:07:16.270 --> 00:07:18.139
I need you to follow
my lead.

169
00:07:20.374 --> 00:07:22.310
[ Groaning ]

170
00:07:22.343 --> 00:07:24.578
[ Chuckles ]
These hatchbacks. huh?

171
00:07:24.612 --> 00:07:26.280
Uh. is that
a dead girl?

172
00:07:26.314 --> 00:07:27.748
[ Chuckles ]
You got me.

173
00:07:27.782 --> 00:07:29.417
Thought this rug would do
the deed.

174
00:07:29.449 --> 00:07:31.786
but it's clearly
not working out.

175
00:07:31.819 --> 00:07:34.889
Ooh. Now. those are
a good idea. Mm.

176
00:07:34.922 --> 00:07:36.891
Wish I'd thought of
60 gallon drums.

177
00:07:36.924 --> 00:07:40.493
Yeah. yeah. they're kind of
industry standard.

178
00:07:40.528 --> 00:07:43.864
Is my face red?
Amateur serial killer here.

179
00:07:43.898 --> 00:07:46.968
Uh. you think maybe
I could buy a couple off you?

180
00:07:47.001 --> 00:07:50.705
Sure.
Uh. retail price is 75 bucks.

181
00:07:50.738 --> 00:07:54.675
Oh. thanks. Saved my night.
Uh. here. I've got 100.

182
00:07:54.709 --> 00:07:56.410
Uh. I don't have
any change.

183
00:07:56.444 --> 00:07:57.812
That's okay. Keep it.

184
00:07:57.845 --> 00:08:00.448
No. no. I'm a killer.
not a thief.

185
00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:05.319
Look. I've got plenty of change
at my place.

186
00:08:05.353 --> 00:08:08.522
It's right down the street.

187
00:08:08.990 --> 00:08:10.257
Oh.

188
00:08:11.592 --> 00:08:13.027
We got to save that girl.

189
00:08:13.060 --> 00:08:16.130
Summer: [ Muffled ]
We got to get those drums!

190
00:08:16.163 --> 00:08:20.134
Hey. dipshit. get on the bus
so I can make fun of you!

191
00:08:20.167 --> 00:08:22.870
You've got the body
of a 14 year old boy.

192
00:08:22.903 --> 00:08:25.206
and I'm gonna beat the shit
out of that body.

193
00:08:25.239 --> 00:08:28.709
Bully is life! I'm gonna make
you so fucking sad.

194
00:08:28.743 --> 00:08:31.779
Yeah. Okay. pal.
Good luck with that.

195
00:08:32.880 --> 00:08:35.449
They're paycheck
to paycheck.

196
00:08:35.483 --> 00:08:37.718
but they keep voting
against their own interests.

197
00:08:37.752 --> 00:08:40.488
I see you.
I know how much pain you're in.

198
00:08:40.521 --> 00:08:42.523
It's not your fault.

199
00:08:42.556 --> 00:08:43.424
[ Sobbing ]

200
00:08:43.457 --> 00:08:45.026
[ Cheering ]

201
00:08:45.059 --> 00:08:47.361
Mr. Goldenfold: And that's why
the Boston Tea Party

202
00:08:47.395 --> 00:08:49.397
sparked
the American Revolution.

203
00:08:49.430 --> 00:08:52.400
Holy integers!
A raised hand.

204
00:08:52.433 --> 00:08:53.467
This is why I only teach math.

205
00:08:53.502 --> 00:08:55.369
History classes
get you canceled.

206
00:08:55.403 --> 00:08:56.971
I just wanted to say

207
00:08:57.004 --> 00:08:58.839
that this history lesson looks
a little different

208
00:08:58.873 --> 00:09:01.008
when you empathize
with all the parties involved.

209
00:09:01.042 --> 00:09:04.278
You take a smart pill?
You're too wise for a child.

210
00:09:04.311 --> 00:09:05.514
Next time I have to sub.

211
00:09:05.546 --> 00:09:07.148
maybe you should do
the teaching.

212
00:09:07.181 --> 00:09:10.317
We should talk about the
real issue here. Mr. Goldenfold.

213
00:09:10.351 --> 00:09:12.153
Your ex-wife. Call her.

214
00:09:12.186 --> 00:09:15.356
You might not get another shot.
but you'll at least get closure.

215
00:09:15.389 --> 00:09:17.658
I wish you were my son.

216
00:09:17.691 --> 00:09:19.528
Hey. can I talk about
how I was bullied in high school

217
00:09:19.560 --> 00:09:20.694
because of my last name?

218
00:09:20.728 --> 00:09:22.129
There's time enough
for everyone.

219
00:09:22.163 --> 00:09:23.697
Principal Vagina.

220
00:09:23.731 --> 00:09:28.803
♪ Thank you. India.
thank you. Providence ♪

221
00:09:28.836 --> 00:09:33.674
♪ Thank you. disillusionment ♪

222
00:09:33.707 --> 00:09:36.644
♪ Thank you. nothingness ♪

223
00:09:36.677 --> 00:09:39.046
♪ Thank you. clarity ♪

224
00:09:39.080 --> 00:09:44.085
♪ Thank you. thank you.
silence ♪

225
00:09:44.118 --> 00:09:46.220
♪ Yeah ♪

226
00:09:47.288 --> 00:09:49.390
♪ Oh. oh ♪

227
00:09:49.423 --> 00:09:56.297
♪♪

228
00:09:56.330 --> 00:10:00.734
Thanks for waiting.
I had to unload the stuff.

229
00:10:01.936 --> 00:10:03.070
Tea?

230
00:10:03.104 --> 00:10:04.171
Sure.

231
00:10:04.205 --> 00:10:07.608
Uh. I don't have to be
worried about this. do I?

232
00:10:07.641 --> 00:10:08.642
[ Chuckles ]

233
00:10:08.676 --> 00:10:11.479
I don't know. Do you?

234
00:10:11.513 --> 00:10:13.314
[ Chuckles ]

235
00:10:13.347 --> 00:10:15.517
[ Laughing ]

236
00:10:15.550 --> 00:10:19.220
Let me get you that change
for the drums.

237
00:10:22.256 --> 00:10:23.691
[ Summer grunting ]

238
00:10:23.724 --> 00:10:27.027
[ Jerry and man laughing ]

239
00:10:27.995 --> 00:10:29.296
Oh!

240
00:10:31.232 --> 00:10:32.399
[ Summer grunts ]

241
00:10:34.468 --> 00:10:35.570
[ Grunts ]

242
00:10:35.604 --> 00:10:38.205
Woman: Hello?
Please let me live.

243
00:10:38.239 --> 00:10:39.640
I'll do anything!

244
00:10:39.673 --> 00:10:40.808
Oh! You're alive.

245
00:10:40.841 --> 00:10:43.644
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!
Help! Help!

246
00:10:43.677 --> 00:10:45.112
Shh. shh. Okay.

247
00:10:45.146 --> 00:10:47.314
Uh. yeah.
I'm gonna get you out of there.

248
00:10:47.348 --> 00:10:48.682
Thank you. Thank you!

249
00:10:48.716 --> 00:10:51.252
If you help me get these
60 gallon drums out of here.

250
00:10:51.285 --> 00:10:52.486
Huh?

251
00:10:52.521 --> 00:10:53.622
[ Slurping ]

252
00:10:53.654 --> 00:10:54.989
Got to say.

253
00:10:55.022 --> 00:10:58.159
you don't seem
like a serial killer.

254
00:10:58.192 --> 00:11:02.730
Oh. I promise I'm
a nightmare person.

255
00:11:02.763 --> 00:11:04.566
The worst of the worst.

256
00:11:04.599 --> 00:11:08.402
Really?
What's your signature?

257
00:11:08.435 --> 00:11:10.572
Ah. My signature.

258
00:11:10.605 --> 00:11:11.972
Uh. what's yours?

259
00:11:12.006 --> 00:11:15.910
I leave a cat toy
in my victim's pockets.

260
00:11:15.943 --> 00:11:19.514
That's why I'm the cat
and mouse killer.

261
